abstract="ICT offers new perspectives in teaching and learning. In this paper a popular non-educational mobile game, ``Pok{\'e}mon Go'', is used as a background for the design of educational activities in Biology, Geography and Mathematics and as a means of informal learning. Five secondary level students (14--15 years old) participated in this study. Data were collected through observation, field notes and interviews. The participants described the activities as attractive, pleasant and creative and stated that there is a lack of engaging learning and technology use in school. The results show that an effective integration of mobile technologies can enhance learning and students' attitude.",
